laboratory_examinations.findings: Suspected ST segment elevation myocardial infarction (STEMI)

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Arteriographic examination of the aortic arch
laboratory_examinations.findings: Occlusion of the brachiocephalic trunk from its origin, and occlusion of the subclavian arteries but permeable renal arteries. Significant stenosis of the left common carotid artery, brachiocephalic trunk, and vertebral vessels at age 13.
